  "topic": "Yield products & aggregators over time",
  "summary": "Historical and current TVL for the major DeFi yield aggregators and yield-trading protocols, sourced primarily from the DefiLlama protocol TVL API (as-of 2026-06-17). The sector's first wave (Yearn, Convex, Beefy) peaked in the 2021 bull market and then bled TVL: Yearn peaked at ~$6.9B (Dec 2021) and is ~$0.15B today; Convex peaked at ~$21.2B (Jan 2022, as the dominant Curve/CRV liquidity layer) and is ~$0.53B today; Beefy peaked at ~$1.3B (Nov 2021) and is ~$0.11B today. The second wave is dominated by yield-trading and curated-vault designs: Pendle (yield/PT-YT tokenization) grew explosively in 2024 (from ~$0.27B in Jan 2024 to a ~$4.4B year-end), set an all-time high of ~$13.4B on 2025-09-19, but has since fallen sharply to ~$1.18B by mid-June 2026 amid a 2026 market drawdown and the wind-down of points/airdrop farming cycles. Morpho (curated lending vaults / Morpho Blue) rose from ~$0.18B (end-2022) to ~$3.25B (end-2024) to a ~$8.5B ATH (Sep 2025), supported by integrations such as Coinbase USDC lending; DefiLlama net TVL is ~$7.1B now (note: Morpho's reported total deposits/supply figures of $10-13B exceed DefiLlama net TVL because they count gross supplied + collateral). All values are USD; series are stated in USD billions. Confidence is high for DefiLlama-derived series (direct API extraction) and medium for third-party deposit/market-share claims.",
